<DOC><DOCNO> AP891030-0101 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-30-89 1343EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-Poll-Method     10-30 0506</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Poll-Method,0520</SECOND><HEAD>Poll on Hostages Based on Phone Interviews</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Poll Hostages, Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   This Media General-Associated Press poll isbased on telephone interviews Sept. 14-24 with 1,071 adults in thecontinental United States. Phone numbers were selected randomly andinterviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recentbirthday, a random phenomenon.   The results were weighted to adjust for variations in thesample. The poll has a 3-point margin of error, meaning that 19 of20 times its findings should be within 3 points of the result ifevery adult American were asked the same questions. The errormargin is larger for subgroups.   There are other sources of potential error in polls, includingthe wording and order of questions. These are the questions in thispoll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100:   1. Do you think of Iran as an enemy of the United States, or asunfriendly but not an enemy, or as something else? Enemy: 47.Unfriendly: 37. Other: 8. Don't know or no answer: 9.   2. Do you think Iran supports terrorism around the world, ornot? Yes: 79. No: 9. DK-NA: 12.   3. Do you think Iran has control over the people who are holdingAmerican hostages in Lebanon, or not? Yes: 72. No: 15. DK-NA: 13.   4. Should the United States offer to resume normal relationswith Iran if Iran gets the American hostages in Lebanon freed? Yes:61. No: 29. DK-NA: 10.   5. The United States has frozen $2 billion in Iranian assets inU.S. banks. Should the United States release this money to Iran ifIran gets the American hostages in Lebanon freed? Yes: 50. No: 37.DK-NA: 13.   6a. Some people say the United States should negotiate with thepeople who are holding American hostages in Lebanon in order to wintheir freedom. Others say negotiating would encourage morehostage-taking. Do you think the United States should negotiatewith the people who are holding American hostages in Lebanon, ornot? Yes: 47. No: 45. DK-NA: 8.   b. (If no) How about if negotiations were held through a thirdparty, such as the Red Cross _ would you support or oppose that?Support: 55. Oppose: 37. DK-NA: 8.   7. Do you think the United States should pay money to thehostage-takers to free the American hostages in Lebanon? Yes: 10.No: 85. DK-NA: 5.   8a. Would you support or oppose the use of U.S. military forcein Lebanon in an effort to free the American hostages in Lebanon?Support: 62. Oppose: 28. DK-NA: 9.   b. (If support) If the hostages might be killed in such anaction _ would you still support it, or not? Yes: 70. No: 24.DK-NA: 6.   9. Do you think the United States government has done enough totry to free the U.S. hostages in Lebanon, or not? Yes: 25. No: 54.DK-NA: 21.   10. Do you think the U.S. hostages in Lebanon eventually will bereleased, or not? Yes: 42. No: 37. DK-NA: 21.</TEXT></DOC>